name: Wat Tan Rice
description: A classic malaysian street food - steamed rice topped with Uncle Lai's famous egg gravy, cooked with pork lard, succulent chicken, juicy prawn, fishcake slices and fresh veggies

name: Fried Rice
description: Uncle Lai's fried rice tossed with wok-hei (breath of the wok). Crunch into crispy pork lard, succulent chicken, egg, juicy prawn, mixed veggies, chinese sausage meat, fishcakes and fresh shallot

name: Wat Tan Hor
description: A malaysian favourite - wok fried rice noodles with succulent chicken, crunchy pork bits, juicy prawn, fishcake slices and fresh veggies, topped off with Uncle Lai's famous silky egg gravy
